---

Hello,
I have discovered a strange bug.

This code works :
```
     reg [7:0]  v_a,v_b,v_c,v_d;
     reg [31:0] v_word;

     v_a = $fgetc(fh);
     v_b = $fgetc(fh);
     v_c = $fgetc(fh);
     v_d = $fgetc(fh);
     v_word = { v_d, v_c, v_b, v_a };

```
But, this code does not (wrong byte ordering) :
```
     reg [31:0] v_word;

     v_word[7:0]   = $fgetc(fh);
     v_word[15:8]  = $fgetc(fh);
     v_word[23:16] = $fgetc(fh);
     v_word[31:24] = $fgetc(fh);

```
This code is part of a testbench and is called inside a task.

Any ideas ? (maybe the compiler changes the calling order due to the -O3 optimization ?).

This is with GCC 4.5.3 not Open64 :-)

Regards,

Frederic Requin

